title: Fearing Awami League comeback, BNP seeks Jamaat support to halt Hasina
description: BNP is seeking support from Jamaat-e-Islami to prevent the Awami League from regaining power in Bangladesh. This move follows the ouster of Sheikh Hasina and claims of her call for armed resistance. Meanwhile, Awami League plans to resume political activities and street protests against the interim government led by Muhammad Yunus.

title: No new limits on Ukraine's use of US arms if North Korea joins fight: Pentagon
description: The US will not impose new limits on Ukraine's use of American weapons amid North Korean military deployments to Russia. NATO's Mark Rutte and the Pentagon have raised concerns about 10,000 North Korean troops in eastern Russia, potentially supporting combat operations against Ukraine near the border.

title: Amid Row Over Hitler Remark, Trump Says He Is "Not A Nazi"
description: Donald Trump told campaign supporters Monday in swing state Georgia that he is "not a Nazi," pushing back on critics' accusations that the Republican is seeking to be an authoritarian American leader.

title: US Voices Disapproval Of Israel Bill Banning UN Palestinian Agency
description: The United States said Monday it was "deeply concerned" about a bill, now passed by Israel's parliament, that bans the UN's Palestinian refugee agency from operating in the country and occupied east Jerusalem.

title: Sudan militia accused of mass killings and sexual violence as attacks escalate
description: Experts fear reports of 124 dead in attack on villages south of Khartoum are significant underestimationSudanese militia have been accused of killings, sexual violence, looting and arson during eight days of attacks on villages south of Sudan’s capital, Khartoum.The UN said there were reports of “gross human rights abuses” linked to the Rapid Support Forces (RSF) group, which has escalated attacks on civilians in el-Gezira state since the area’s key commander was reported to have defected to government forces on 20 October. title: Shirley Ayorkor Botchwey appointed Commonwealth secretary general
description: Ghana’s foreign minister since 2017, Botchwey supports calls for reparations for transatlantic slavery and colonialism Commonwealth members have appointed Ghana’s foreign minister, Shirley Ayorkor Botchwey, as the new secretary general, on the final day of the group’s summit in Samoa.Botchwey, a former lawmaker who has served as Ghana’s foreign minister since 2017, has supported calls for reparations for transatlantic slavery and colonialism – a position that was also shared by the two other candidates who had vied for the position.
